				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aburr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1299372); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1299372&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204242" alt="Aburr" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1299372)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aburr" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1299372); return false;" >Aburr</a></span> <span class="odate time_1337710619 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 May 2012 18:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1456475">
									

<p>Yeah, this is cute enough to get an upvote. The meter (meter?) on two of the rhymes looks slightly off to me, though I can't claim to know shit about that sort of thing and certainly might be wrong:</p>
<p><em>&quot;What marvels are in His remaking!<br />
What wonders are in Her control!<br />
His Broken Gears turn forever<br />
restoring the penitent soul!&quot;</em></p>
<p>I think it matches if you make &quot;turn&quot; into &quot;turning&quot;, and&#8230;</p>
<p><em>&quot;We are His Clockwork Servants!<br />
We do the work of His hand!<br />
Those who oppose will forgive us<br />
when they are made to understand!&quot;</em></p>
<p>Changing the last line to &quot;when they at last understand&quot; likewise makes this flow better in my head. Anyways, yes, I like it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
