					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tunedtoadeadchannel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304457); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=304457&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204242" alt="tunedtoadeadchannel" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=304457)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tunedtoadeadchannel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304457); return false;" >tunedtoadeadchannel</a></span> <span class="odate time_1343724557 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Jul 2012 08:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1523586">
									

<p>Depends where you put the emphasis. When I wrote it, I emphasized the first syllable of &quot;broken&quot;. Adding a syllable to &quot;turn&quot; and de-emphasizing &quot;broken&quot; also works, I suppose, though I prefer to keep it in an active tense rather than passive, because I want to give the line a feeling of power.</p>
<p>Same kinda dealie on the last line, only I disagree with your version way more; I used &quot;they are made to understand&quot; because from the CotBG's perspective, the mission is exactly that; remove the oppositions very <em>ability</em> to disagree. As far as meter, it's an eight count like the end line of each, though it splits differently. If you stress &quot;they&quot;, it flows okay.</p>

							</div>

								
					
